I wanted to create a new thread, for those of you who want to be challenged, questioned, angered, and not. And for those of you who see it is &quot;that damn spatz&quot; and what to pass on by: I think I have a couple of items for your interest:<br>
#1:The wounds of war - appeared in the Orange County Register Newspaper yesterday. Letter to the editor, in a very Libertarian paper:<br><br>
As a Vietnam War veteran, like so many, I have held a resentment for Vietnamese people and all people of Asian descent for almost 30 years.<br><br>
It wasn't until I formed a chapter of Vietnam Veterans of America, Inc., in Long Beach that I started to learn how grateful the Vietnamese were for our troops having tried to keep their country from becoming a communist country.<br><br>
It happened last weekend in Westminister, as I was working as a volunteer at &quot;The Wall,&quot; the half-scale replica of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial in Washington, D.C. At the same time, in the same park Vietnamese were remembering the loss of their country to communism.  After their ceremony was over, the Vietnamese color guard marched down the walkway, maybe 1,000 yards, to where &quot;The Wall&quot; was on display. The<br>
color guard was followed by about 500 Vietnamese people, young and old, who came to pay their respects to the Americans who gave their lives to protect Vietnam. After everyone had left, all that could be seen was a sea of  flowers and flags that were left by the Vietnamese. <br><br>
I would like to thank the whole Vietnamese community of Southern California for all the healing that this one simple act has done.  Max Stewart - Long Beach<br><br>
